import os
import numpy as np
import StringIO
import matplotlib

matplotlib.use('Agg')

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
def show(p):
    img = StringIO.StringIO()
    p.savefig(img, format='svg')
    img.seek(0)
    print '%html ' + img.buf

paragraphs.title: Simple Linear Regression
paragraphs.text:
studentScores =np.array([[95,85],[85,95],[80,70],[70,65],[60,70],[55, 50]])
X = studentScores[:,0]
Y = studentScores[:,1]
meanX, meanY = studentScores.mean(0)

divationX = X - meanX
divationY = Y - meanX

varianceX = ((X - meanX) ** 2).sum()

beta = (divationX.dot(divationY) / varianceX)
alpha = meanY - beta * meanX

print "alpha={0},beta={0}".format(alpha, beta)

newY = alpha + X * beta

print newY

plt.clf()
plt.subplot(2, 1, 1)
plt.title("Regression Line")
plt.ylabel("Statistics")
plt.scatter(X, Y, color='red')
plt.plot(X, newY, "b-")

plt.subplot(2, 1, 2)
plt.title("Predict")
plt.xlabel("Math")
plt.ylabel("Statistics")
plt.scatter(75, alpha + 75 * beta, color='green')
plt.scatter(85, alpha + 85 * beta, color='gray')
plt.plot(X, newY, "b-")
show(plt)
plt.close()

paragraphs.title: Simple Linear Regression by try Error
paragraphs.text:
plt.clf()
plt.figure(figsize=(20, 20))

errors = []
index = 0
betas = np.arange(0, 1, 0.05)
for beta in betas:
    index += 1 
    alpha = meanY - beta * meanX
    newY = alpha + X * beta
    error = (((Y - newY) ** 2).sum() / len(Y)) ** 0.5
    errors.append(error)
    
    plt.subplot((len(betas)/3)+1, 3, index)
    plt.subplots_adjust(hspace=1)
    plt.title("beta={0}, error={1}".format(beta, error))
    plt.scatter(X, Y, color='red')
    plt.plot(X, newY, "b-")
    
show(plt)
plt.close()

bestErrorIndex = np.array(errors).argmin()
print("The best ß is {0} and its error is {1}".format(betas[bestErrorIndex], errors[bestErrorIndex]))
